JOHANNESBURG - NUM (the National Union of Mineworkers) has condemned Sibanye Gold s decision to dismiss more than 2,000 workers at its Cooke operations in Westonaria.READ: Sibanye Gold fires 1,500 mineworkers over illegal strikeThe union has vowed it will use all its resources to force the company to reverse its decision.The miners were fired for taking part in a wildcat strike over a company drive to root out illegal miners.READ: More than 200 illegal miners arrested at Cooke mineSome workers were arrested for providing illegal miners with food underground.But NUM, insists its over 1,000 members were coerced to participate by rival union AMCU.eNCA